# 2026-07-08 overnight security hardening (SOC2 AI-code-security research,
# docs/security/AI_CODE_SECURITY_RESEARCH_2026-07-07.md).
#
# save-exact: lockfile pins exact versions (no ^/~ ranges) for anything
# newly installed here, closing the gap where a compromised/malicious
# transitive dependency could slip in via a semver-range bump between
# audits.
#
# ignore-scripts: ENABLED 2026-07-08 daytime session, after a fuller audit
# than the overnight note below found. Corrected record: the overnight pass
# only checked sharp and assumed Prisma was safe because `npx prisma
# generate` runs as an explicit Dockerfile step -- that's true for CLIENT
# GENERATION but doesn't cover @prisma/client's and @prisma/engines'
# postinstall scripts (query-engine binary fetch) or prisma CLI's preinstall.
# Full audit (scanned every node_modules/**/package.json for an install/
# postinstall/preinstall script):
#   sharp            install:      node install/check.js || npm run build
#   esbuild          postinstall:  node install.js   (tsx's transform
#                     engine -- esbuild is in tsx's OWN dependencies, not
#                     server/package.json's devDependencies entry, so it
#                     survives `npm prune --omit=dev` in the runtime
#                     Dockerfile and matters in production)
#   @prisma/client   postinstall:  node scripts/postinstall.js
#   @prisma/engines  postinstall:  node scripts/postinstall.js
#   prisma (CLI)     preinstall:   node scripts/preinstall-entry.js
#   unrs-resolver    postinstall:  node postinstall.js  (jest-only --
#                     `npm ls unrs-resolver --omit=dev` -> empty, pruned
#                     from every production image; a local-dev-only
#                     concern, not a Docker-build one)
# The first 5 are all reachable from production dependencies and matter for
# a real boot. Fix: server/Dockerfile, Dockerfile.migrate, and Dockerfile.prod
# each got an explicit `npm rebuild <pkgs> --foreground-scripts` step right
# after `npm ci` (npm rebuild re-runs a named package's lifecycle scripts
# regardless of ignore-scripts -- that config only suppresses the automatic
# run during install/ci). Verified via a real build + boot + functional
# check on the ServiceCycle VPS before flipping this flag on -- see
# CLAUDE memory servicecycle-daytime-2026-07-08.md for the verification log.
save-exact=true
ignore-scripts=true
